Delegates to the Southeastern Interfraternity Council elected University of Tennessee student Arthur vonWerssowetz senior in business as president of the council at their convention in Atlanta Feb PERIOD  PERIOD

Attending the previous years convention sparked vonWerssowetzs interest in running for president he said PERIOD

 he said PERIOD

During the election vonWerssowetz made a threeminute speech to members of the voting body composed of IFC presidents from each school PERIOD Then two delegates were allowed to speak on his behalf PERIOD

One of those delegates was Chaz Molder junior in political science and IFC secretarytreasurer at UT PERIOD

Molder said vonWerssowetzs election resulted from the dedication he has shown to the fraternity system PERIOD

 Molder said PERIOD

VonWerssowetz said while in office he plans to increase communications between participating SEIFC schools PERIOD

 vonWerssowetz said PERIOD

During his term of office he will be responsible for coordinating the programming for the  SEIFC convention and will act as a communications link between participating schools PERIOD

 vonWerssowetz said PERIOD

Molder said that UTs IFC will benefit from vonWerssowetzs election PERIOD

 Molder said PERIOD

His work as UTs IFC president helped him to prepare for his new role vonWerssowetz said PERIOD

 vonWerssowetz said PERIOD
